   hospitalization analysis. Results: There were 111 patients (62.4\%)
   physically frail, amongst those 48 (43.2\%) had depressive symptoms.
   Only 1 patient had depressive symptoms without frailty. There was an
   additive effect of depressive symptoms and physical frailty on
   nutritional status. For the groups with no frailty, frail but no
   depressive symptoms, and frail with depressive symptoms, serum albumin
   decreased in a stepwise manner (35.8 +/- 5.6, 34.9 +/- 4.4, and 32.9 +/-
