   19.42), 14.05 (IQR 3.57 - 37.27), and 26.62 (IQR 10.65 - 61.18) days per
   year of follow up, respectively (p <0.0001). Conclusion: Physical
   frailty and depressive symptoms are both common in Chinese PD patients,
   and they have additive adverse effect on the nutritional status and
